This paper is primarily focused on object detection using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses modifications to the network architecture to improve performance, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the detection of vehicles, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the use of convolutional features, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
